## 🛠️ How to Use

### Getting Started
1. Open `index.html` in your web browser
2. You'll see the main ToDoList interface

### Adding a Task
1. Enter your task in the input field
2. Click the "Add" or "Create" button
3. Task appears in your list

### Managing Tasks
- **Complete Task**: Click the checkbox or task item to mark as done
- **Edit Task**: Click the edit icon/button to modify the task description
- **Delete Task**: Click the delete/trash icon to remove the task

### Data Persistence
- Tasks are automatically saved to browser localStorage
- Your tasks will remain even after refreshing or closing the browser
- Clear local storage to reset all tasks

---

## 💻 Technologies Used

| Technology | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| **HTML5** | Structure and semantic markup |
| **CSS3** | Styling and responsive design |
| **JavaScript (Vanilla)** | Core functionality and DOM manipulation |
| **LocalStorage API** | Data persistence |

---

## 📝 Code Highlights

### Key JavaScript Functions
- `addTask()` - Add new task to list
- `deleteTask()` - Remove a task
- `editTask()` - Modify task content
- `toggleComplete()` - Mark task completion
- `saveToLocalStorage()` - Persist data
- `loadFromLocalStorage()` - Retrieve saved tasks

---

## 🎨 Customization

You can customize the app by modifying:
- **Colors**: Edit CSS color values
- **Fonts**: Change font-family in styles
- **Layout**: Adjust grid/flexbox properties
- **Features**: Add new functions in JavaScript

---

## 📱 Browser Support

Works on all modern browsers that support:
- HTML5
- CSS3
- ES6 JavaScript
- LocalStorage API

✅ Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge

---

## 🐛 Known Limitations

- Single-user offline application
- No cloud sync capability
- Limited to browser storage capacity (~5-10MB)
- No categories or priorities system (can be added)

